            <pb n="1"/>
            <p><add>?</add> MSS. p. 20, note 16 (continued)</p>
            <p>vide everything necessary for our religious worship. When<lb/> with the advice of his
                assistants shall from time to time<lb/> propose such regulations as may be necessary
                for the good<lb/> government of the society. He shall be obliged to call his<lb/>
                junta the <date>first Sunday in every month</date> and keep a book of<lb/> their
                proceedings wrote in a legible hand and good manner;<lb/> which book shall be laid
                before the members at large when-<lb/>ever he is requested to do it (by a majority).
                No rules or<lb/> regulations shall be considered as binding on the
                congre-<lb/>gation until it is read 2 <date>shabbath</date> or holidays separately
                in<lb/> the synagogue, Should any member object to the same it must<lb/> be by a
                letter to the parnas within 24 hours after the last<lb/> publication, who shall be
                obliged to call a meeting of all<lb/> the members in town, when a majority present
                at such meeting,<lb/> which must be 2<lb/>3 of the members in town, shall
                    <sic>deterim</sic><lb/> the same and the <sic>teremination</sic> shall be
                binding on the objecting<lb/> member (and all the rest). He shall give four copies
                of the<lb/> laws now made with the proceedings of the juntas shall be
                de-<lb/>livered to his successor with all books and papers belonging<lb/> to the
                congregation. He shall when a yahid has a son born<lb/> give him the distribution of
                all the mitzvoth on the following<lb/>
                <date>shabbath</date> and must be called for the sefer. And when his wife<lb/> comes
                to shul after lying-in of a son or a daughter, must be<lb/> called to the sefer.</p>
            <p>4. The duty of the assistants shall be to assist the parnas in<lb/> the execution of
                his office. They shall be obliged to attend<lb/> him on the <date>fourth Sunday of
                    every month</date>; and report to the<lb/> congregation <hi rend="underline">any
                    improper conduct that they may observe by</hi><lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">him</hi>, and such complaint to be laid before the Yahidim
                for</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>MSS. p. 20, note 16 (concluded)</p>
            <p>their determination.</p>
            <p>5. In the absence of the parnas the senior assistant shall<lb/> officiate and so in
                rotation the 7 hathan torah and in his<lb/> absence the hathan bereshith.</p>
